==English==
===Etymology===
From "pearl diving", it being imagined the surfer is diving down for pearls.
===Adjective===
# (''surfing'') digging the nose of one's [[surfboard]] into the water, often on takeoff.
#: 1999: ''Used a pointed tip today and learned why I kept pearling with my round tipped board. Round noses like to dig into the water, causing frustrating wipeouts.'' &mdash; Joanne VanMeter [http://www.letsplay.net/archive99/020399.shtml]
